<div class="panel-container">
  <div class="panel students-bg"></div>
  <h1 class="title"> For Students </h1>
  <p class="white subtitle">
    Joining Blueprint is the perfect way to use skills you've learned in the
    classroom to give back to the community.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="white-bg">
  <div class="spacer-small"></div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 medium-9 columns">
      <p id="hook">
        We are an organization of passionate UC Berkeley students
        who develop web and mobile applications for non-profit organizations.
        As a member, you will be able to join a family of likemineded students
        working to use our education and technological prowess to make the
        world a better place.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="small-12 medium-3 columns" id="apply-button">
      <% if @settings.student_app_open %>
        <%= link_to "Apply Now", new_student_application_path, class: "button" %>
      <% else %>
        <div class="applications-closed">
          <p>
            Applications are now closed for this semester. Thank you for your interest!
          </p>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="spacer-small"></div>
</div>

<div class="gray-bg">

  <div class="spacer-large"></div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="title-column">
      <h1>Application Process</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="content-column">
      <div class="small-12 columns">
        <ul class="timeline-vertical">
          <li class="work timeline-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <h5 class="title">Infosessions</h5>
              <span class="date"><h5>TBA</h5></span>
              <span class="circle"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p>Come out and talk to us
                to learn more about Blueprint at one of our infosessions.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="work timeline-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <h5 class="title">Applications Due</h5>
              <span class="date"><h5>TBA</h5></span>
              <span class="circle"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p>Fill out the online application. Our inital cuts will be based
                on the application and will be emailed out ASAP.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="work timeline-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <h5 class="title">Blueprint Games</h5>
              <span class="date"><h5>TBA</h5></span>
              <span class="circle"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p>A fun little event for you guys
                to flex your problem solving muscles in a team of other applicants. Second round
                cuts will be based on this event.</p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="work timeline-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <h5 class="title">Behavioral Interviews</h5>
              <span class="date"><h5>TBA</h5></span>
              <span class="circle"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <p>The final step in the applicaiton process, we really want to feel your passion for social good
                in person. Final decisions will be announced from this event.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="small-12 columns decision-criteria">
        <div class="spacer-small"></div>
        <h4 class="title">Decision Criteria</h4>
        <p>If we could, we would accept every applicant but unfortunately we cannot manage the volume of people and administrative overhead while still fulfilling our mission to the best of our abilities. The following criteria are what we use to evaluate applicants.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Passion</strong>
            <p>This is the single most important criteria. Do you demonstrate a genuine passion for social good?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Skill</strong>
            <p>Do you have the necessary skills to productively contribute to the mission?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Experience</strong>
            <p>Do you have relevant work experience? Volunteering experience?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Attitude</strong>
            <p>Do you demonstrate positive, hard-working attitude?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Teamwork</strong>
            <p>Do you display the ability to work well in a team?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Culture</strong>
            <p>Will you get along well with the rest of Blueprint? We’re sure you will!</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="spacer-large"></div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="title-column">
      <h1>FAQ</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="content-column">
      <div class="small-12 columns" id="faq">
        <div class="drawer">
          <h5>What is Blueprint's project structure? <span>(+)</span></h5>
          <p>
            The client and the project leader communicate on a weekly basis to ensure the
            project’s progress. Meetings occur throughout the project engagement, beginning with
            at least one mandatory project scoping meeting with the project leader at the onset.
            A formal midpoint presentation will be given in Week 5 of the engagement, and the final
            recommendation will be delivered at a final presentation in Week 10.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="drawer">
          <h5>How are client team interactions conducted? <span>(+)</span></h5>
          <p>
            The client and the project leader communicate on a weekly basis to ensure the
            project’s progress. Meetings occur throughout the project engagement, beginning with
            at least one mandatory project scoping meeting with the project leader at the onset.
            A formal midpoint presentation will be given in Week 5 of the engagement, and the final
            recommendation will be delivered at a final presentation in Week 10.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="drawer">
          <h5>What resources does Blueprint have to ensure success? <span>(+)</span></h5>
          <p>
            The client and the project leader communicate on a weekly basis to ensure the
            project’s progress. Meetings occur throughout the project engagement, beginning with
            at least one mandatory project scoping meeting with the project leader at the onset.
            A formal midpoint presentation will be given in Week 5 of the engagement, and the final
            recommendation will be delivered at a final presentation in Week 10.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="spacer-large"></div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
      <h2>Want to be involved?</h2>
      <p class="subtitle">Sign up for our newsletter to get updates about events, our work and applications!</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-8 small-centered columns">
      <form>
        <div class="newsletter-form tooltip-item">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Email Address" disabled></input>
          <button type="submit" disabled>Go</button>
          <div id="full-page-tooltip" class="tooltip"><p>Pardon our dust, this is still under construction.</p></div>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="spacer-small"></div>
</div>
